        <h1>LeetCode 3623: Smallest Substring With Identical Characters II (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given a binary string s of length n and an integer numOps. You are allowed to perform the following operation on s at most numOps times: Select any index i (where 0 &lt;= i &lt; n) and flip s[i], i.e., if s[i] == '0', change s[i] to '1' and vice versa. Return the minimum length of the longest substring of s that consists of only identical characters after performing at most numOps operations.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: s = "000001", numOps = 1<br/>
                Output: 2<br/>
                Explanation: By changing s[2] to '1', s becomes "001001". The longest substrings with identical characters are s[0..1] and s[3..4].<br/><br/>
                Input: s = "0000", numOps = 2<br/>
                Output: 1<br/>
                Explanation: By changing s[0] and s[2] to '1', s becomes "1010". The longest substring with identical characters is of length 1.<br/><br/>
                Input: s = "0101", numOps = 0<br/>
                Output: 1<br/>
                Explanation: No operations are needed. The longest substring with identical characters is of length 1.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int minLength(string s, int numOps) {
        int n = s.length();
        
        auto canAchieve = [&amp;](int maxLen) -&gt; bool {
            // Try for both '0' and '1' as the target character
            for (char target : {'0', '1'}) {
                int ops = 0;
                int i = 0;
                
                while (i &lt; n) {
                    if (s[i] == target) {
                        // Move forward by maxLen
                        i += maxLen;
                    } else {
                        // Need to flip this character
                        ops++;
                        i++;
                    }
                    
                    if (ops &gt; numOps) break;
                }
                
                if (ops &lt;= numOps) return true;
            }
            
            return false;
        };
        
        int left = 1, right = n;
        int result = n;
        
        while (left &lt;= right) {
            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
            
            if (canAchieve(mid)) {
                result = mid;
                right = mid - 1;
            } else {
                left = mid + 1;
            }
        }
        
        return result;
    }
};</code></pre>
